item.title: CVE-2018-20236|2024-09-16T19:10:38.203Z -- atlassian -- sourcetree%20for%20windows
item.description: There was an command injection vulnerability in Sourcetree for Windows from version 0.5a before version 3.0.10 via URI handling. A remote attacker could send a malicious URI to a victim using Sourcetree for Windows to exploit this issue to gain code execution on the system.

item.title: CVE-2019-11582|2024-09-16T19:25:35.218Z -- atlassian -- sourcetree%20for%20windows
item.description: An argument injection vulnerability in Atlassian Sourcetree for Windows's URI handlers, in all versions prior to 3.1.3, allows remote attackers to gain remote code execution through the use of a crafted URI.
